cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on traffic load balancing in mobile networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a framework for balancing network utilities and green energy utilization, which involves control and optimization of system parameters. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed framework is implemented as a virtually distributed algorithm, which involves distributed computing and communication. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the trade-off between on-grid power consumption and average traffic delivery latency, which can be modeled using game theory. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the optimization of network performance metrics, which can be analyzed using information theory.
